<style type="text/css">
    table, th, td { border: 1px solid black; }
</style>

<div dir="ltr">
  <h1>
    Peak Load Update
    </h1>

    Today’s Risk of the Annual Peak is
    <%= @report.actual_forecast.risk.capitalize %>

    <table class="waffle" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tbody>
            <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <td class="s0" dir="ltr" colspan="10">
                    The following table is intended as a guide to help entities anticipate when the annual peak load for the ISO-NE system will occur and to make their own decisions about whether and when to load shed.
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <td class="s0" rowspan="2"></td>
                <td class="s1" dir="ltr" colspan="1">TODAY</td>
                <td class="s1" dir="ltr" colspan="7">NEXT 6 DAYS</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <%- @report.forecasts.each do |forecast| %>
                    <td class="s2" dir="ltr"><%= forecast.date %></td>
                <%- end %>
            </tr>
            <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <td class="s1 softmerge" dir="ltr">
                    <div class="softmerge-inner" style="width: 97px; left: -1px;">
                        ISO-NE Estimates:
                    </div>
                </td>
                <td class="s4" colspan="9"></td>
            </tr>
            <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <td dir="ltr">High Temp (oF)</td>
                <%- @report.forecasts.each do |forecast| %>
                    <td dir="ltr">
                        <%= forecast.high_temp %>
                    </td>
                <%- end %>
            </tr>
             <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <td class="s0" dir="ltr">
                    Peak Hour
                </td>
                <td class="s1" dir="ltr">
                    <%= @report.forecasts.first.peak_hour.strftime("%l%P") %>
                </td>
                <td class="s13" colspan=6></td>
            </tr>
            <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <td class="s0 softmerge" dir="ltr">
                    <div class="softmerge-inner" style="width: 97px; left: -1px;">
                        Peak Load (MW)
                    </div>
                </td>
                <%- @report.forecasts.each do |forecast| %>
                    <td dir="ltr">
                        <%= number_with_delimiter(forecast.peak_load, delimiter: ",") %>
                    </td>
                <%- end %>
            </tr>
            <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <td class="s1 softmerge" dir="ltr">
                    <div class="softmerge-inner" style="width: 97px; left: -1px;">
                        Today’s Risk of the Annual Peak
                    </div>
                </td>
                <%- @report.forecasts.each do |forecast| %>
                    <td dir="ltr">
                        <%= forecast.risk.capitalize %>
                    </td>
                <%- end %>
            </tr>
           <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <td class="s0" dir="ltr" colspan="10">
                    The “Risk of the Annual Peak” rating is generated by MAPC based on a comparison of the estimated Peak Load for the day reported by ISO-NE and load on historic annual peak days. It is a recommendation only.
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr style='height:20px;'>
                <td class="s0" dir="ltr" colspan="2">UNLIKELY &lt;22,500 MW</td>
                <td class="s0" dir="ltr" colspan="4">POSSIBLE 22,500-23,500 MW</td>
                <td class="s0" dir="ltr" colspan="4">LIKELY &gt;23,500 MW</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>

